title: Lady Cougars Regular Season End 3-14 Record
text: Lady Cougars Regular Season End 3-14 Record Posted: 10/20/2015 06:37:19 PM MDT Updated: 10/20/2015 06:44:16 PM MDT Senior Aspen Lanckriet, labero, gets a dig during Friday s loss against Caliche. (Courtesy photo) Junior Jessica Kler blocks in the middle (Courtesy photo) The Sedgwick County Cougar Volleyball team were defeated by Leyton, Akron, and Caliche this last week during their matches. This was the last week of regular season games for the Lady Cougars. The girls were able to take Leyton to four matches after a hour long delay of the game. This was parent's night for the volleyball girls, and they were able to ring in a winning set. Although, they stayed with Leyton, they fell 19-25, 25-22, 16-25, and 25-16. Losing to Akron on Thursday's away game in three sets: 19-25, 15-25, and 18-25. The Lady Cougars stuck with the Rams throughout the set, but just couldn't finish a rally. On Friday, during the away conference match against Caliche the Cougars were defeated in three sets by 25-12, 25-23, and 25-9. Senior Sierra Kline hits in the front row during Friday s game. (Courtesy photo) Falling just short of winning the second set the momentum was lost. The Cougars end their regular season with a 3-14 record. Districts will happening in the weeks to come.
